<p>I just uploaded the interview that I did with Nasir Gebelli in 1998 at my company, Ion Storm, during an Apple II Reunion that I hosted. There's a lot of great information about his history in the industry and how he got started.</p><p>Nasir wrote games entirely in assembly language and did not save source code. He didn't even have a printer to look at his code! He wrote all his NES games on an Apple II and cross-developed them to the NES hardware. Even the SNES game, Secret of Mana, was coded on an Apple II, in 65816 assembly with no source.</p><p>I've been talking to Nasir recently about doing an in-depth interview. If you have any particular questions you'd like answered, please put them in the comments or email me at john at romero dot com.</p><p><a href="https://rome.ro/news/2017/2/7/nasir-gebelli-interview-on-youtube">Permalink</a><p>]]></description><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/566d855a841abafcc8ed19c4/1486452515890-H5B8UFZUGO73FG9LXKU7/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kJetqQzT0xn_LSf7zuN_19ZZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWQUxwkmyExglNqGp0IvTJZamWLI2zvYWH8K3-s_4yszcp2ryTI0HqTOaaUohrI8PIE7-HwavAnzj3GUer4BDq6mZuyLgP5iaow1wLyajCHPs/Screen+Shot+2017-02-07+at+07.26.50.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="958" height="663"><media:title type="plain">Nasir Gebelli Interview on YouTube</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Site Updating</title><dc:creator>John Romero</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 30 Dec 2016 16:42:28 +0000</pubDate><link>https://rome.ro/news/2016/12/30/site-updating</link><guid isPermaLink="false">566d855a841abafcc8ed19c4:566d86c02399a3bdabbc9bdf:58668d65cd0f6809622a7a00</guid><description><![CDATA[<figure class="
